name="venue">Colloquium, HoTTEST Summer School 2022</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>There is a considerable distance between the formal rules of type theory and the code that you must write in order to animate them as a running program. In this colloquium, you will learn the basic techniques of type theoretic implementation in the OCaml programming language, including the representation of syntax as well as type-directed conversion.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:contributions></fr:contributions><fr:context></fr:context><fr:related></fr:related><fr:backlinks></fr:backlinks><fr:references></fr:references></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>